    "Some of the prominent activation functions that are widely used are presented in Table 5.",
    "Pooling layerA down-sampling operation must be done on each feature map in a pooling or subsampling layer.",
    "A pooling layer is characterized by a formation that preserves the image features while simultaneously reducing the image size.",
    "Additionally, it stores image information.",
    "This subsequent step is to use a pooling function, such as maximum, global, or average, with a kernel size or pool size that has already been set for each of the feature maps [125]."
